The lectures cover following topics: 1) geographical and geopolitical position of the East Asian countries (China, Taiwan, Korea, Japan); 2) ethnic composition, linguistic diversities and conformities of the East Asian nations; 3) East Asia as an integrated cultural region and historical causes of its forming; 4) main features of the cultures of the East Asian nations in their comparison; 5) politics and economy of the East Asian countries and their mutual relations; 6) the position and role of the East Asian nations in today's world.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the course is to provide basic knowledge on the area studies, history, and cultures of the-East-Asian countries (China, Taiwan, Korea, Japan) as well as their mutual relations and position and role in today's world.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student who has passed this course: 1) has a systematic view and basic knowledge on the geography, languages, cultures, and mutual relations of the East Asian nations and is able for comparative analysis of them; 2) is able to orientate in the theoretical matters and basic concepts of the East Asian studies; 3) is able to use obtained knowledge in her/his further studies in the field of Far-Eastern languages, history, cultures etc.; 4) is able to apply this knowledge in the practice and independently complete and develop them from the prospect of her/his major field of study.
